cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with language modeling and word prediction. The use of external knowledge to generate expressive context representations suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of attention mechanism and the large scale experimental study suggest that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
